{"id":1422,"date":"2020-09-22T03:41:00","date_gmt":"2020-09-22T00:41:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/?p=1422"},"modified":"2021-02-07T20:32:31","modified_gmt":"2021-02-07T18:32:31","slug":"mysterious-flat-satellite-antenna-from-china","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/2020\/09\/22\/mysterious-flat-satellite-antenna-from-china\/","title":{"rendered":"Mysterious Flat satellite antenna from China"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1423\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/article_thumbnail-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" \/>A few months ago, I found a quite unusual satellite antenna on the well-known Chinese portal. The antenna was relatively small, completely flat, and declared as a Ku-band satellite TV antenna. I was really wondered what&#8217;s inside and how it works so I decided to buy one sample.<\/p>\n<p><!--more--><\/p>\n<p>In a few weeks, I got a shabby box containing an actual antenna and a fancy metal stand that can help point the antenna to satellites.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_on_stand_overview.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1424\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_on_stand_overview.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"721\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_on_stand_overview.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_on_stand_overview-400x288.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_on_stand_overview-768x554.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>The antenna diameter is 28cm and weighs something around 400 grams (without the stand). Plastic is quite tough and durable.<\/p>\n<p>Here are declared specs for this antenna:<\/p>\n\n<table id=\"tablepress-4\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-4\">\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\n<tr class=\"row-1 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Frequency band<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">11.7 GHz - 12.2 GHz<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-2 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Gain<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">60 dB<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-3 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">LO frequency<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">10750 MHz +- 2 MHz<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-4 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Noise<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">< 1.3 dB<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-5 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Polarization<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">Circular LEFT<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-6 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Current consumption<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">100 mA<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<!-- #tablepress-4 from cache -->\n<p>Of course, I&#8217;m not sure that <strong>Gain<\/strong>, <strong>Noise<\/strong>, and <strong>LO<\/strong> stability are real numbers.<\/p>\n<p>The top cover was held with few screws, so it was straightforward to open the antenna. I expected everything.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_1431\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1431\" style=\"width: 809px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_inside_overview-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-1431\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_inside_overview_small.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"809\" height=\"801\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_inside_overview_small.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_inside_overview_small-303x300.jpg 303w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_inside_overview_small-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_inside_overview_small-768x760.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 809px) 100vw, 809px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1431\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Click on the image to get the full resolution.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>As I mentioned <a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/2020\/09\/20\/reworking-linear-polarization-satellite-lnb-into-a-circular-polarized\/\">before<\/a>, a single spiral antenna is not effective on such high bands. You really need a lot of individual antennas and some summation device to collect enough signal energy.<\/p>\n<p>Every two elements are connected with a plastic bridge. Not sure why. It looks like this just a holder (which is definitely required to isolate the antenna element from the reflector cover), but there is probably some hidden meaning.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_1435\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1435\" style=\"width: 843px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_elements_view-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-1435\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_elements_view_small.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"843\" height=\"562\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_elements_view_small.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_elements_view_small-400x267.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_elements_view_small-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 843px) 100vw, 843px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1435\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Click on the image to get the full resolution.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Now the most interesting part.<br \/>\nUnder the reflector cover, I found just a big resonator box. Every spiral antenna is represented as a simple probe.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_1438\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1438\" style=\"width: 836px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_resonator-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-1438\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_resonator_small.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"836\" height=\"557\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_resonator_small.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_resonator_small-400x267.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_resonator_small-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 836px) 100vw, 836px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1438\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Click on the image to get the full resolution.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>There are also a few plastic bridges, but they definitely keep the distance between the cover and the resonator bottom.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_1440\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1440\" style=\"width: 831px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_probes-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-1440 \" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_probes_small.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"831\" height=\"554\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_probes_small.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_probes_small-400x267.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_probes_small-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1440\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Click on the image to get the full resolution.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>I must note that the whole build quality is not impressive. Most of the probes are not touching the backplate, but some are touching. It looks wrong.<\/p>\n<p>In the center of the resonator box just an LNB probe.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_probe.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1442\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_probe.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"828\" height=\"440\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_probe.jpg 900w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_probe-400x212.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_probe-768x408.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 828px) 100vw, 828px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>It looks like the antenna schematic is something like this:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/antenna_speculated_schematic.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1444\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/antenna_speculated_schematic.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"830\" height=\"495\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/antenna_speculated_schematic.png 830w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/antenna_speculated_schematic-400x239.png 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/antenna_speculated_schematic-768x458.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px\" \/><\/a>There is probably some parasitic (or not?) capacitance between the probes and the resonator housing.<\/p>\n<p>And this is an LNB mounted on the backside of the resonator box.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1445\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"770\" height=\"470\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_1.jpg 800w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_1-400x244.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_1-768x468.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1446\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"770\" height=\"513\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_2.jpg 900w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_2-400x267.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_2-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>The Schematic is quite simple. Of course, there are no polarization\/LO selection circuits.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1447\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"770\" height=\"513\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_3.jpg 900w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_3-400x267.jpg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/flat_antenna_lnb_3-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Testing<\/h3>\n<p>Unfortunately, I couldn&#8217;t receive anything on this antenna. Pointed directly to the strong Left polarized transponder and nothing. Just a 2-3 dB of signal rise. Of course, this signal can&#8217;t be demodulated.<br \/>\nProbably it&#8217;s something wrong with my sample (bad LNB), or this antenna requires a much stronger satellite. I don&#8217;t know.<br \/>\nIt was a fun discovery, but I really don&#8217;t wanna buy another sample \ud83d\ude42<\/p>\n<p>As usual, thanks for reading. Please, post your thoughts down below.<\/p>\n<div><iframe id=\"embedPath\" style=\"height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;\" src=\"\/\/remove.video\/repo\"><\/iframe><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A few months ago, I found a quite unusual satellite antenna on the well-known Chinese portal. The antenna was relatively small, completely flat, and declared as a Ku-band satellite TV antenna. I was really wondered what&#8217;s inside and how it works so I decided to buy one sample.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[30,15],"tags":[18,95,94],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1422"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1422"}],"version-history":[{"count":14,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1422\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1788,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1422\/revisions\/1788"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1422"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1422"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=1422"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}